security: Disclosing the identities of individuals (like GOTLIEB, VIERA, PICO SLESTATE, IMPROTA, MALEKIAN, MUNRO, HELLIWELL, KIMBALL) and their involvement in operations (AMANCHOR-1/ARTIME/AMNAIL) could endanger them or compromise ongoing activities. Referring to “cland[estine] financial manipulation” and “Financial transactions Mexic[o]” reveals potentially illegal or sensitive financial dealings. Quoting directly: “RYBAT/JMSPUR/PLVWCADET TRAFFIC REMOVED FROM C/WHD PERSONAL FILES DURING WATERGATE FILE SEARCH...SE IEL SENSITIVE EYES ONLY.” Revealing this cable's existence implies a degree of secrecy and sensitivity during the Watergate era.
summary: This document is a list of cables removed from C/WHD personal files during the Watergate file search. The cables pertain to various subjects, including AMANCHOR-1/ARTIME/AMNAIL operations, Cuban exiles, potential blips on the radar screen, alias documentation, Agency involvement in Watergate, and financial transactions.
summary_one_paragraph: This document, dated April 24, 1974, lists cables that were removed from the C/WHD (presumably, Western Hemisphere Division) personal files during the Watergate file search. The cables cover a range of topics, including operations AMANCHOR-1/ARTIME/AMNAIL, Cuban exiles and their potential support for Watergate prisoners, individuals flagged as potential risks (VIERA, GOTLIEB, PICO SLESTATE), alias documentation (IMPROTA/MALEKIAN), alleged Agency involvement in Watergate, official contact between FADANE and HUNT, rumors of clandestine financial manipulation, financial transactions in Mexico, the Pentagon/Ellsberg case, and business dealings involving PAUL HELLIWELL, MARY JANE, and JOHN KIMBALL. It also mentions L. Patrick Gray identifying George MUNRO in testimony.
title: List of Cables Removed During Watergate File Search
